# Supabase SSR for Next.js App Router

Use `@supabase/ssr` for Next.js App Router. Reference: https://supabase.com/docs/guides/auth/server-side/nextjs

## Client usage

- **Browser (Client Components)**: Use `createClient()` from `@/lib/supabase/client` (uses `createBrowserClient`)
- **Server (Server Components, Route Handlers, Server Actions)**: Use `createClient()` from `@/lib/supabase/server` (uses `createServerClient` with cookies)

## Auth protection

- Always use `supabase.auth.getClaims()` to protect pages and user data — never trust `getSession()` in server code
- `getSession()` does not revalidate the JWT; `getClaims()` validates the signature against project public keys

## Middleware

- Middleware refreshes auth tokens via `updateSession` in `@/lib/supabase/proxy`
- Return the `supabaseResponse` object from middleware — do not create a new response without copying cookies
